    "name": "The Millennials Fukuoka",
    "detail": "I had an absolutely wonderful stay at The Lively 2 months ago, while it was summer in Japan. I came back during autumn & wanted to try their pods. Positive: LOCATION. Best advantage of the hotel as it is w/in short walking distance to the subway, which is connected to the airport. Their area is pretty much awake. A lot of convenience stores and restaurants are open 24 hrs. CLEANLINESS. The hotel is relatively new. They just opened July this year. FRIENDLY STAFF, well personally, I find Japanese people helpful, polite and friendly. AND, you still have access to their free daily beer for 1 hr and unlimited coffee at their coworking lounge. Not so Positive: NO PROJECTOR in the pods. NO COMPLIMENTARY WATER BOTTLE. Only available for The Lively guests. TEMPERATURE. We found the pods really warm. We were sweating! They said they are trying to ctrl the temp as it was cold outside. Should've just maintained a cool temp. In the pods u have the option to close the fan anyway & u have blanket",
